The paper is about a framework for robotics simulations, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses Bayesian inference and likelihood-free inference methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The framework is designed to improve the accuracy of simulations, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions domain randomization, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) to improve the robustness of models.
